1
00:00:41,679 --> 00:00:42,520
What's going on?

2
00:00:49,399 --> 00:00:50,960
That explosive earlier

3
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,280
must've been too powerful.

4
00:01:10,760 --> 00:01:11,480
Godfather!

5
00:01:12,319 --> 00:01:13,120
An Xiang!

6
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:15,000
Godfather!

7
00:01:16,079 --> 00:01:19,000
An Xiang, are we both dead?

8
00:01:19,519 --> 00:01:20,319
No.

9
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:22,760
Lucky these giant mushrooms cushioned us.

10
00:01:22,959 --> 00:01:24,319
We're both perfectly fine.

11
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:27,439
Where on earth are we?

12
00:01:28,319 --> 00:01:29,159
Oh my God.

13
00:01:29,959 --> 00:01:31,959
We fell from such a great height

14
00:01:31,959 --> 00:01:33,200
and somehow survived.

15
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:35,239
It's nothing short of a miracle.

16
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:36,519
Who's that over there?

17
00:01:37,799 --> 00:01:38,599
Brother Chen!

18
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:40,760
Brother Chen!

19
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:44,079
Brother Chen!

20
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:46,640
Didn't expect you'd actually

21
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:49,560
end up lying down before me.

22
00:01:59,319 --> 00:02:00,040
Godfather!

23
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,400
What are you doing?

24
00:02:17,039 --> 00:02:17,639
I...

25
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:24,199
Get up!

26
00:02:26,439 --> 00:02:27,080
Hey...

27
00:02:28,199 --> 00:02:29,280
Who do you think I am?

28
00:02:31,159 --> 00:02:32,199
Wake up! Wake up!

29
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:33,639
Where are the others?

30
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,199
Right over there.

31
00:02:38,599 --> 00:02:39,879
Acting all weird.

32
00:02:42,199 --> 00:02:43,400
How are you? You okay?

33
00:02:43,759 --> 00:02:44,439
Are you alright?

34
00:02:44,439 --> 00:02:45,039
I'm fine.

35
00:02:53,439 --> 00:02:54,439
Where is this place?

36
00:02:54,919 --> 00:02:57,360
Brother, you're asking me?

37
00:02:58,599 --> 00:03:00,960
Didn't you blast the rocks loose?

38
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:02,479
And that's why we fell down here?

39
00:03:02,479 --> 00:03:03,439
How would we know?

40
00:03:12,719 --> 00:03:13,599
Where's Uncle Min?

41
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,280
Why can't I see Uncle Min anywhere?

42
00:03:15,439 --> 00:03:16,439
No idea.

43
00:03:16,439 --> 00:03:18,159
He wasn't here when we woke up.

44
00:03:18,319 --> 00:03:19,759
You actually care about him?

45
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:21,080
Isn't it better that he's gone?

46
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:23,400
Cut the chatter. Find everyone first.

47
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,080
By the way, An Xiang...

48
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:34,759
Do you remember if your mismatched eyes

49
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,400
were something you were born with,

50
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:38,840
or did they suddenly change one day?

51
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:42,000
I can't really remember my childhood.

52
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:43,280
All I remember is

53
00:03:43,919 --> 00:03:45,560
before my godfather adopted me,

54
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:46,840
I was already like this.

55
00:03:51,159 --> 00:03:53,120
This Chiyan Jizhou is one creepy place.

56
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:54,000
Look at these mushrooms.

57
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,240
Every single one is massive.

58
00:03:56,199 --> 00:03:57,199
That's nothing.

59
00:03:57,199 --> 00:03:59,479
I've heard there's a giant fungus abroad,

60
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:01,439
the Armillaria ostoyae,

61
00:04:01,879 --> 00:04:03,719
as big as 1,600 football fields.

62
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,719
The little girl picking mushrooms,

63
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:12,120
carrying a big bamboo basket,

64
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:16,839
barefoot in the early morning,

65
00:04:17,759 --> 00:04:20,560
roaming the woods and hills.

66
00:04:21,839 --> 00:04:24,519
The little girl picking mushrooms,

67
00:04:25,319 --> 00:04:29,160
carrying a big bamboo basket.

68
00:04:31,319 --> 00:04:33,120
Brother's having quite a good time here.

69
00:04:33,759 --> 00:04:34,480
Uncle Min!

70
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:35,959
Come down!

71
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:38,480
How could he possibly get down?

72
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:40,199
I'll help him.

73
00:04:40,199 --> 00:04:40,879
Catch him, alright?

74
00:04:40,879 --> 00:04:43,120
The mushroom picker...

75
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:57,319
No, no.

76
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,319
I... I told him to catch you.

77
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:03,759
I didn't know you'd fall from there.

78
00:05:06,959 --> 00:05:07,920
My godfather.

79
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:09,800
What's wrong with him?

80
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:10,720
Don't worry.

81
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:12,959
Your godfather ate a mushroom by mistake.

82
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,319
The mushrooms here are toxic.

83
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:15,399
They cause hallucinations.

84
00:05:15,399 --> 00:05:16,519
But his life isn't in danger.

85
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,839
Everyone be careful.

86
00:05:18,079 --> 00:05:19,160
I have experience with this.

87
00:05:19,519 --> 00:05:22,079
Any mushroom that's brightly colored

88
00:05:22,079 --> 00:05:22,879
is poisonous.

89
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:24,240
Whether a mushroom is poisonous

90
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:26,480
can't be judged just by how bright it is.

91
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:28,000
That's just a folk myth.

92
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:29,959
If you really want to know,

93
00:05:29,959 --> 00:05:31,480
you need precise identification.

94
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,480
Precise, my foot.

95
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:33,879
If you ask me, just watch what you eat.

96
00:05:33,879 --> 00:05:34,959
Don't eat them and you'll be fine.

97
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:36,480
Exactly.

98
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:38,959
That's what I mean.

99
00:05:39,279 --> 00:05:41,240
Control yourself.

100
00:05:41,519 --> 00:05:45,079
So tell me, what actually happened?

101
00:05:45,079 --> 00:05:48,600
When did you cut all your hair off?

102
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:52,160
Godfather, wake up, Godfather.

103
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,759
It's me, An Xiang, Godfather.

104
00:05:58,480 --> 00:05:59,399
I'm An Xiang.

105
00:05:59,399 --> 00:05:59,879
Yes, yes, yes.

106
00:05:59,879 --> 00:06:00,759
An Xiang.

107
00:06:01,839 --> 00:06:03,120
An Xiang, An Xiang.

108
00:06:04,399 --> 00:06:05,920
Why are you here?

109
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:09,199
You, I don't want to see your eyes.

110
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:10,360
Your eyes.

111
00:06:11,079 --> 00:06:12,720
Hold him, soothe him, soothe him.

112
00:06:12,879 --> 00:06:13,639
Comfort him.

113
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,519
Gently, gently, gently.

114
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:18,040
Sing a little tune, a little tune.

115
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:19,319
There, there.

116
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:22,160
Clap your hands

117
00:06:23,279 --> 00:06:25,199
in the first month.

118
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,920
The old lady wants...

119
00:06:28,879 --> 00:06:30,879
It worked. He's asleep.

120
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:34,720
By the way, I just checked.

121
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:36,199
We fell down from above.

122
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,720
I don't know how deep we fell.

123
00:06:38,319 --> 00:06:40,680
Luckily, the altar's at the very bottom.

124
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,439
As long as we keep heading down,

125
00:06:42,439 --> 00:06:43,319
we can't go wrong.

126
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:45,120
How do we find it?

127
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:47,360
These caves are holes within holes,

128
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,360
paths within paths.

129
00:06:49,439 --> 00:06:50,879
The caves we found earlier

130
00:06:50,879 --> 00:06:52,120
at least had stone steps.

131
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:53,480
But this place, just mushrooms everywhere.

132
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,079
Like we walked into a restaurant kitchen.

133
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,199
While scouting just now,

134
00:06:57,199 --> 00:06:58,480
I found a stream over that way.

135
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:59,480
If we follow the water,

136
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:00,480
we should be fine.

137
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,680
Bi Huaqiang, take care of your master.

138
00:07:02,759 --> 00:07:03,399
Let's move out.

139
00:07:10,879 --> 00:07:11,800
Old Chen.

140
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:14,800
I know I've said this many times,

141
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,800
but I have to say it again.

142
00:07:17,319 --> 00:07:18,680
You're really something.

143
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:07,680
Run! Quick, run, hurry!

144
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:08,120
Go!

145
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:11,720
Run, Godfather!

146
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:12,279
Run!

147
00:08:13,199 --> 00:08:13,759
Go!

148
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,319
Hurry!

149
00:08:22,439 --> 00:08:23,879
Get on the mushrooms, quick, quick!

150
00:08:29,839 --> 00:08:30,800
What's going on?

151
00:08:30,839 --> 00:08:32,320
Maybe when we blasted the mountain,

152
00:08:32,639 --> 00:08:34,120
it damaged the rock structure here.

153
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,120
They're thousands of years old.

154
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:36,679
How could they withstand such an impact?

155
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:37,720
So what do we do?

156
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,120
Find a way out.

157
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:59,000
Run!

158
00:09:09,279 --> 00:09:10,240
Is it following us?

159
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:11,960
No.

160
00:09:13,639 --> 00:09:16,080
I've never heard of water forming snakes.

161
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:17,759
That's just not scientific.

162
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:20,080
Forget scientific or not for now.

163
00:09:20,519 --> 00:09:21,840
Let's find the others.

164
00:09:22,279 --> 00:09:22,879
Move!

165
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:33,919
Hurry, hurry!

166
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:42,919
Shutong, you go first.

167
00:10:21,159 --> 00:10:21,799
Uncle Min

168
00:10:21,799 --> 00:10:22,519
Godfather

169
00:10:23,799 --> 00:10:25,639
Don't call me that, it's Master Lu

170
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:27,000
Look at this

171
00:10:27,639 --> 00:10:28,320
Take a look

172
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:30,279
What is this?

173
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:32,399
It's a huge claw print

174
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:33,960
Now look over here

175
00:10:34,879 --> 00:10:39,639
One, two, three, four

176
00:10:40,759 --> 00:10:42,799
Four prints in one set

177
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:46,120
This must be some massive reptile

178
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:49,559
If the prints are this big

179
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,799
how huge must the creature be?

180
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:54,000
Let's not go any further

181
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:57,320
Mengna Valley's been buried for millennia

182
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:58,360
So a creature this big

183
00:10:58,360 --> 00:10:59,679
isn't really that surprising

184
00:11:00,039 --> 00:11:00,879
Not just in Nanyun

185
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,519
Yunling has these too

186
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:05,480
Maybe it's caused by radiation

187
00:11:05,519 --> 00:11:06,320
Right

188
00:11:06,799 --> 00:11:08,440
Let's not go any further

189
00:11:08,559 --> 00:11:09,879
Then we came here for nothing.

190
00:11:09,879 --> 00:11:11,799
Don't be scared, we're here. Let's go

191
00:11:26,159 --> 00:11:27,279
It's so hot

192
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:28,399
Wait a sec

193
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:32,519
Look at the prints, here's one

194
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:34,279
heading forward

195
00:11:35,879 --> 00:11:40,159
This means the creature went that way

196
00:11:40,399 --> 00:11:42,000
We should go this way

197
00:11:42,919 --> 00:11:44,039
Master Lu, hurry up

198
00:11:47,679 --> 00:11:48,679
Come on, faster

199
00:11:48,919 --> 00:11:49,559
Okay

200
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,039
Advisor He! Advisor He!

201
00:11:56,159 --> 00:11:57,320
Come over here, quickly!

202
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:01,559
Fatty, protect Advisor He

203
00:12:01,559 --> 00:12:02,519
I'll lure the snake away

204
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:23,879
Holy crap

205
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:37,080
Advisor He

206
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:41,399
Godfather, slow down

207
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:49,720
Uncle Min

208
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:51,919
Something's not right

209
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:54,639
Why is it getting hotter the further we go?

210
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,200
You're not the only one

211
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:57,879
I'm feeling really hot too

212
00:13:01,919 --> 00:13:02,799
What's that sound?

213
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:12,879
What...

214
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:13,960
What is that?

215
00:13:14,399 --> 00:13:15,559
A lizard, I guess

216
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,879
Does it... does it eat people?

217
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:23,799
Technically speaking

218
00:13:23,799 --> 00:13:26,399
normal-sized ones don't eat humans

219
00:13:26,799 --> 00:13:29,559
But this one's way too big!

220
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:32,600
I think we should run!

221
00:13:36,360 --> 00:13:38,159
What kind of lizard breathes fire?

222
00:13:38,559 --> 00:13:39,879
Once you enter Chiyan Jizhou

223
00:13:39,879 --> 00:13:41,799
there's no shortage of strange creatures

224
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,519
In our biology elective, they said

225
00:13:43,679 --> 00:13:45,759
there's a fire-breathing fish on an Indian island

226
00:13:45,879 --> 00:13:47,200
When it senses danger

227
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:48,320
it spews out flames

228
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,440
On Indonesia's Java Island

229
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:50,519
there's also a fire-breathing frog

230
00:13:50,519 --> 00:13:52,639
It ejects a kind of volatile oil

231
00:13:52,639 --> 00:13:54,000
that self-ignites in mid-air

232
00:13:55,519 --> 00:13:57,159
Stop, stop with the "there's also"

233
00:13:57,159 --> 00:13:58,799
If you're so smart, put out that fire!

234
00:13:59,559 --> 00:14:00,279
Godfather

235
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:03,279
Just one has us cornered already

236
00:14:03,279 --> 00:14:05,399
What if another one shows up?

237
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:06,960
This lizard

238
00:14:07,399 --> 00:14:09,399
must be Mengna Valley's guardian beast

239
00:14:09,639 --> 00:14:10,360
Seeing it means

240
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:12,480
we're just one step away from the altar

241
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:14,000
One step away, two steps away,

242
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,519
what's that got to do with me?

243
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:18,320
My motto is: see danger, retreat

244
00:14:18,559 --> 00:14:20,600
We're this close to succeeding now

245
00:14:20,919 --> 00:14:21,639
You know

246
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:24,399
to gain what ordinary people can't gain

247
00:14:24,759 --> 00:14:25,559
you must endure

248
00:14:25,559 --> 00:14:27,519
hardships ordinary people can't endure

249
00:14:27,519 --> 00:14:29,559
You want success, you endure it

250
00:14:29,559 --> 00:14:30,879
I don't want success

251
00:14:30,879 --> 00:14:31,919
This kid is so young

252
00:14:31,919 --> 00:14:33,639
Is she gonna get roasted alive with you?

253
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,039
An Xiang
